                    Risk 2 — too many controls on screen 
                    Cause: 
                         •    exposing all options at once 
                    Fix: 
                         •    keep defaults simple, hide advanced controls 
                    Risk 3 — notation rendering works inconsistently 
                    Cause: 
                         •    poor serialization/rendering assumptions 
                    Fix: 
                         •    validate early with real generated examples 
                    Risk 4 — guided sessions feel random 
                    Cause: 
                         •    weak template or curriculum logic 
                    Fix: 
                         •    enforce phase structure, mode weights, and full-session validation 
                    Risk 5 — beginner mode is still too hard 
