       Final Advice 
       The biggest risk now is feature creep. 
       Your app is already approaching the complexity of a serious jazz training tool. That’s 
       good — but only if the interface stays simple. 
       Rule to follow: 
       One screen = one musical idea. 
       Never mix multiple concepts on the same page. 
        
       UI Principles for This App 
        1.  One concept per screen – each page teaches one musical idea. 
        2.  Same layout for every exercise page – users shouldn’t relearn the UI. 
        3.  Controls first, score second – configure → generate → practice. 
        4.  Minimal controls visible initially – advanced settings hidden. 
        5.  Fast regeneration – users will press regenerate constantly. 
                                             
