                    One last important design tip 
                    The score viewer is the core of the app. Everything else is secondary. 
                    Make sure: 
                         •    the score is large 
                         •    spacing is clean 
                         •    regeneration is fast 
                    Users will spend 90% of their time looking at the score, not the controls. 
                     
                     
                    Now we define the visual design system so the app stops being “a bunch of screens” 
                    and starts feeling like one product. 
                    This matters more than people think. A weak design system creates: 
                         •    inconsistent spacing 
                         •    random typography 
                         •    clutter 
                         •    UI drift as features grow 
                    For your app, the design should feel: 
                         •    calm 
                         •    focused 
                         •    musical 
                         •    modern 
                         •    minimal 
                    Not flashy. Not enterprise. Not “AI dashboard.” 
                                                                                                                                                 
                    1. Design Direction 
                    Product personality 
                    The app should feel like: 
                         •    a practice companion 
                         •    a music notebook 
                         •    a clean studio tool 
                    It should not feel like: 
                         •    a finance dashboard 
                         •    a gaming app 
                         •    a social app 
                         •    a dense academic theory website 
                    Visual tone 
                    Use a style that is: 
                         •    dark UI shell 
                         •    bright notation area 
                         •    restrained accent color 
                         •    soft contrast 
                         •    rounded but not bubbly 
                    That combination works well because music notation needs a light surface, while the 
                    rest of the app can be calm and dark. 
                                                                                                                                                 
                    2. Color System 
                    Use a small color palette. Too many colors will make the app look amateur. 
       Core palette 
       Background 
       App Background:    #0F172A 
       Surface Background:#111827 
       Card Background:   #1E293B 
       Muted Surface:     #334155 
       These give you a dark, controlled base. 
       Text 
       Primary Text:      #E2E8F0 
       Secondary Text:    #94A3B8 
       Muted Text:        #64748B 
       Inverse Text:      #0F172A 
       Accent 
       Choose one main accent only. 
       Recommended: 
       Primary Accent:    #38BDF8 
       Accent Hover:      #0EA5E9 
       Accent Soft:       #E0F2FE 
       This blue feels modern and calm without looking generic. 
       Success / warning / error 
       Success:           #22C55E 
       Warning:           #F59E0B 
       Error:             #EF4444 
       Use these rarely. 
       Special notation surface 
       The notation area should be light: 
       Score Background:  #FFFFFF 
