                    This is non-negotiable. Staff notation on dark backgrounds usually looks worse and is 
                    harder to read. 
                                                                                                                                                 
                    3. Semantic Color Usage 
                    Define strict rules. 
                    Accent blue is for: 
                         •    primary buttons 
                         •    active tabs 
                         •    selected items 
                         •    sliders 
                         •    focused controls 
                    Green is for: 
                         •    completed practice 
                         •    success messages 
                         •    streak indicators 
                    Orange is for: 
                         •    warnings 
                         •    unfinished setup 
                         •    attention states 
                    Red is for: 
